message.text:
Brasil: July 19 How to make "KAWAII" OBENTO
ブラジル：7/19　カワイイお弁当講座
http://fjsp.org.br/

OBENTO is a single-portion meal common in Japanese cuisine. By making riceballs look like pandas, tomatoes like an apple, or by simply using colorful ingredients and cute cutting designs, your lunchtime shall become even more exciting and enticing! 
In Japan, we commonly say we eat food with your eyes, not your mouth - "me de taberu" 目で食べる. You can guess why!

message.text:
Tsuyu（梅雨（つゆ）, rainy season, literally translated as "plum rain") is just around the corner in Tokyo. 
Japanese rainy season lasts only about a month around June with soft rain, except Hokkaido. (Hokkaido doesn't have Tsuyu!)
What do you do when rain last? Why don't we enjoy the rainy season with new rain boots & umbrella, and sing in the rain!
東京ではもうすぐ梅雨の季節！雨の日が続いたら、何をして楽しみましょうか？
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1737&p=1&q=つゆ&source=search&lang=en

message.text:
Have you ever watched Japanese silent films?
Starting from May 30, the Japan Foundation is presenting silent film screenings, with katsudo benshi or katsuben (活弁：live narration for silent films, a very unique aspect of Japanese film culture) and musical accompaniment, in two cities in Switzerland and in three cities in Spain.
http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/culture/media/oversea/1405/05-01.html
活動弁士と伴奏付きの無声映画上映会、スイスとスペインで開催！5/30から。
